  Adaon rubs his chin thoughtfully.  ">Magic<, eh?  Aye, the bards 
dabble in >magic<.  We dinnae use it so much as a tool for combat, but 
as a toy, a tool for entertainment.
  "O' course, if ye ha' nae heard me say it before:  a bard is nae a 
thing if not imaginative.  Some o' these bairns come up with the most 
ingenious uses for simple magicks.  But on the other hand, it is nae 
something we depend on.  A bard relies on his wit, >talents<, and 
>music< more than >magic<.  That is the province o' the mages.
  "Do ye have any another question for me?"
